<subSubSection id="F882EBFA83761704FF24FE70B82BF2E3" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B027B87183761704FF24FE70B82BF2E3" blockId="3.[136,1452,464,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="7798C3F283761704FF24FE70B81FF19F" authorityName="Cornejo &amp; Lombardi. A, Cerro Azul" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,286,464,485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Salacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="juradoi">
<emphasis id="82EC646383761704FF24FE70B81FF19F" box="[136,286,464,485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Salacia juradoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species from coastal 
<collectingCountry id="C88FF8E183761704FDE5FE70BB98F19C" box="[585,665,464,486]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
that resembles 
<taxonomicName id="7798C3F283761704FC9EFE70BD86F19F" authority="(Miers.) A. C. Sm." authorityName="A. C. Smith" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="Miers." baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[818,1159,464,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Salacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="impressifolia">
<emphasis id="82EC646383761704FC9EFE70BAC6F19F" box="[818,967,464,485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">S. impressifolia</emphasis>
(Miers.) A. C. Sm.
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the opposite to decussate arrangement of leaves, larger leaf blades, narrowly oblong to oblong, sometimes narrowly-lanceolate, 
<quantity id="7760159483761704FB53FE54BC5EF273" box="[1279,1375,500,521]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" unit="cm" value="22.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="14.0">14–30 cm</quantity>
(versus elliptic, rarely ovate, obovate or lanceolate, [3.4–] 
<quantity id="7760159483761704FD30FDB7BA12F257" box="[668,787,535,557]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.21" metricValueMax="1.42" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" unit="cm" value="12.1" valueMax="14.2" valueMin="10.0">10–14.2 cm</quantity>
), margin with scattered dark-brown marginal glands (vs. eglandular), flower buds oblate, light-green, white-pulverulent (versus globose, ferrugineous), margin of sepals often ciliate or ciliolate (vs. glabrate), petals patent, erose (vs. deflexed, entire), outer margin of disk entire (vs. fimbriate), and fruit with pericarp smooth (vs. verrucose).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
